review_blob: Great crispy malts and hops - nice nose that has some faint floral tones and a nice dash of citrus. Very refreshing beer.
Beautiful golden orange pour into a snifter from a can. Nice 2 inch head leaves a lot of lacing. Nose is perfect and nice on the palate. One of the ebst XXIPA I have ever had. Will buy again.
This is a fantastic IPA and the ABV is perfect at 7.25%. Really nice nose with a nice amber/copper colr. Beautiful head that leaves a lot of nice lacing. This is an exceptional beer!

Wow! Fantastic Belgian . . . wonderfull grass, meadow, pear aromas . . .  palate is perfect (its got some zing but not too carbonated - perfect). Appearance is crisp straw/golden with a BIG  4 finger head of medium size bubbles that settles down to a one finger. This is a DELICOUS beer! Off to buy more tomorrow.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Tank 7 Farmhouse Ale

beer_brewer_name: Old Dominion Brewing Company (Coastal Brewing Co.)
review_blob: Nice beer but high pine predominates over other more nuanced flavors. Pours nice and head/lacing is good. Very dry (even for a DIPA). would buy again.
Huge creamy head; Huge hops;good malt backbone; piney nose and finish. One of the best examples of a DIPA I have ever had. Near perfect.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Double Wide I.P.A.

review_blob: Nice pils without a TON of character but perfect for a session beer. Like this beer.
This is surely my Go to IPA!  Love the slight malty backbone and the nice dry hoppy finish. ABV is well hidden!

Bought a couple cases at $9.99 each closeout. Good purchase at that price but not a huge fan of this beer. Spicey notes of Coriander, kind of acidic on the palate. Nothing to write home about. Nose is fresh and citrusy. Small head dissipates fast. Nice goldenrod color.

Nice ruby read appearance. Draft pour in a dimple mug at Cheers Boston. Decent head, some lacing. Goes down smooth and has a little aftertaste. Nice session beer while in Boston for a few days! Not much nose.
Big ABV (10%) - caramel hop bomb. Best beer I have had in a long time. Super smooth palate. Takes a while to sip and svor. Incredible beer. Changed my opinion about beer in a can forever.

Love this brewery! Never had a bad bew from these guys. The flagship of this brewery is the Brooklyn Lager. Pours copper with nice head and tastes like a lager should - malty but not too heavy. Taste is cramel and almonds (light). Nose is resiny and hints of citrus. Near perfect beer.

Hop Bomb! BIG citrus and pine hops and a nice balance of caramel malts. Orange/copper pur into a pint glass. Decent head and good lacing. Nice fiesty carbonation but not overpowering. Great dry resiny finish. A yummy beer.

Nice copper hue, small head that dissapears quickly, mild lacing. Tastes mainly malty with a nice hop bite - hops are mainly herbal, malt is mainly cereal and slight caramel and bread notes.  Body is medium, texture is creamy with average carbonation finish is bitter but not overpowering. Nice representation of the style.
Love this beer! Perfect lager on a warm day. Grassy malts and a bit of bitter. Nice golden color and earthy aroma. Solid head and adequate lacing. Nice sesion beer.

Out of the can into a pint glass - nice nose (caramel and mild citrus). Orange color with a nice 2 finger head that dies fairly quick down to a slim white topper. Little carbonation but nice lacing. Goes down smooth as silk with big malt backbone nicely balanced with bitter hops. Not a hop bomb at all - a near perfect balance of malt and hops. Will buy again.
beer_name: 21st Amendment Brew Free or Die IPA

review_blob: This is a sleeper . . . really nice on the palate and not too watery for a macro brew. Has some nice mild sweetness to it - low-average carbonation - goes down smooth and easy. Nice session beer and nice to have a 12p on hand at all times. Way better than most macro beers but its not a big flavor or aroma bomb. Better than most in the inexpensive lager cat. Worth the price
NIce mix but more IPA - the yeast of the Belgian makes it very interesting. Soft on the palate but with moderate carbonation. Nice beer, Would buy again.

Pours a golden orange with a nice head and really nice lacing. Big hoppy beer but a serious maly back bone that almost is too much for a DIPA. Still, its apricot nose and taste mixes well with citrus and some oine needle. Not a typical DIPA but really tasty with a big punch at 9.0 ABV. Smooth palate with mild carbonation makes it go down smooth and nice. Will buy again.

Beautiful in the trappist glass  . . . dark chesnut roasty taste and look with a big head that really lingers - sugary lacing lingers too. To roasted for me but if you like the bready beers this is a great one to check out. 9.0ABV is well hidden. Will buy again in the late fall/early winter.

Golden amber in color, nice nose but not pronounced. The head is a nice 2 finger which lingers. Some lacing in the trappist glass. Very clean with just a tocuh of bitter bite (more bitter than malty). Nice floaties on the bottom of the glass (non-pasteurized). A very fulfilling ale which I will buy again.

Nice crisp summer brew. I like the look in the glass (dirty but deep straw yellow - more yellow than straw). Nose is ok. Palate is very crisp/clean/grassy notes/touch of lemon but barely. OK head, mild lacing. Very tasty from bottle to pilsner glass. Would buy again (esp when its 92 and high humidity!)

After 30+ IPAs  . . . no contest, the best I have had thus far. Can not believe its in a can! The visual in the glass is a orange sunrise and slightly cloudy. Beautimous!  Hoppy? YES. Bitter? Kind of. But an extremely  smooth mellow taste. Goes down too easy!  Nose? Insane apricots and oranges and mild tangerine. Palate is amazingly smooth. Nice ABV that is VERY well hidden but there nonetheless. I would give it a perfect score but Im pnly 45 and there so many IPAs! Paid 12 for a 4pk of tall boys. Will be back for more tomorow!
beer_name: Oskar Blues Deviant Dales India Pale Ale

review_blob: Im more of an IPA guy, but need to venture out occasionally to the malty side of things. This did the trick - this is a SUPERB beer. Big bread, molasses, and caramel notes. Lots of fruit and the Alcohol is not overpowering though fairly high. A huge head and tons of lacing. A quality beer that is surely one of the best of its type worldwide

This is an incredible beer - nicely balanced with good hoppy character and just the right amount of malt to balance. Beautiful golden look, nice 2 finger head that leaves some nice lacing. Nice ABV @ 7.5 and its well hidden. This has become my favorite over the last few months. A beer that bears repeated quaffing :)
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob:
holy crap - where do I start? 

Aroma: tangerines and apricots, open flowery meadows, slight pine, some orange peel, slight tobacco, very fruity, alcoholy esters, nice.

Appearance: Deep copper, nice head, major lacing.

Taste: fruit forward, dry finish, tight at the end, the 11.5 % alcohol is there in a good way but nice and soft,.

Palate: Perfect - mild carbonation thats not in the way.

Overall: Killer brew that looks, smells, and tastes great and will sneak up on you and club your head.
beer_name: Flying Dog Double Dog Double Pale Ale

review_blob: UPDATED: JUN 6, 2012
beer_name: Flying Dog Imperial IPA - El Dorado Single Hop

review_blob: WOW! Killer black IPA. Bitter with a nice coffee hint. Big head that fades to a nice half finger top. Great lacing. Nice toastee IPA! Mild carbonation.

Perfect for the English Bitter Ale style . . . must have one if you have never tried it. Nice and bitter and with a nice malt character too. Nice copper color - great creamy head and decent lacing as you drink. Very good representation of the style. (14.9 oz can into a pint glass).
Nice example of the style - malty but the ABV warms the hops nicely. Very nice deep copper color. Bread, carmel, sugary and hoppy! Nice lacing and huge creamy head. Near perfect!
beer_name: Samuel Adams Third Voyage Double IPA

review_blob: UPDATED: SEP 21, 2012
beer_name: Laughing Dog Sneaky Pete Imperial IPA
